The Management require the Municipal Treasurer to:

1. Immediately record the reconciling items on the cash books to facilitate proper reconciling of books and deposit the balance remaining balance to the authorized government depository bank;

2. Post every collections and deposits in a chronological order and update her cash book on a daily basis;

3. Coordinate with the Municipal Accountant to facilitate regular reconciling the cashbook balances and the books of account of the LGU quarterly to facilitate early detection of errors and immediate correction thereof;

4. Deposit the collection intact and faithfully comply with existing laws, rules and regulations in the collection and deposit of all income of the LGU to ensure that all monies received are fully accounted and properly recorded in the books of accounts and avoid possible loss and/or misuse of the scarce government funds; 

5. Institute adequate internal control system to facilitate proper monitoring on the movement of accountable forms per accountable officer; prepare and submit on time the RAAF and CRAAF; and conduct periodic physical inventory on accountable forms to facilitate verification of CRAAF balances; and

6. Require the Municipal Accountant to draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to take up those reconciling items that will affect the cash and other accounts.

